snippet: Alaska expanded federal Medicaid coverage after the state’s highest court on Monday refused an appeal by the State Legislature to halt Gov. Bill Walker’s expansion order.
abstract: Alaskan Gov Bill Walker's order to expand federal Medicaid coverage proceeds after Alaska Supreme Court refuses appeal by State Legislature to halt plan; Republican-controlled Legislature had sought temporary restraining order while filing lawsuit to permanently block expansion.
lead_paragraph: Alaska expanded federal Medicaid coverage after the state’s highest court on Monday refused an appeal by the State Legislature to halt Gov. Bill Walker’s expansion order.

headline.main: Alaska: Aided by Governor, Medicaid Coverage Grows
headline.print_headline: Alaska: Aided by Governor, Medicaid Coverage Grows
